README.md
     1‚Üí# dotenv
     5‚ÜíDotenv is a zero-dependency module that loads environment variables from a `.env` file into [`process.env`](https://nodejs.org/docs/latest/api/process.html#process_process_env). Storing configuration in the environment separate from code is based on [The Twelve-Factor App](https://12factor.net/config) methodology.
     6‚Üí
     7‚Üí[Watch the tutorial](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YtkZR0NFd1g)
     8‚Üí
     9‚Üí&nbsp;
    10‚Üí
    11‚Üí## Usage
    13‚ÜíInstall it.
    14‚Üí
    15‚Üí```sh
    16‚Üínpm install dotenv --save
    17‚Üí```
    18‚Üí
    19‚ÜíCreate a `.env` file in the root of your project:
    20‚Üí
    21‚Üí```ini
    22‚Üí# .env
    23‚ÜíS3_BUCKET="YOURS3BUCKET"
    24‚ÜíSECRET_KEY="YOURSECRETKEYGOESHERE"
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
    39‚Üí## Advanced
    43‚ÜíImport with [ES6](#how-do-i-use-dotenv-with-import):
    44‚Üí
    45‚Üí```javascript
    46‚Üíimport 'dotenv/config'
    47‚Üí```
    48‚Üí
    49‚ÜíES6 import if you need to set config options:
    50‚Üí
    51‚Üí```javascript
    52‚Üíimport dotenv from 'dotenv'
    53‚Üídotenv.config({ path: '/custom/path/to/.env' })
    54‚Üí```
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   319‚Üí## Agents
   323‚Üí> Software is changing, and dotenv must change with it‚Äîthat is why I built [agentic secret storage (AS2)](https://dotenvx.com/as2). Agents run code without humans at terminals, so plaintext `.env` files are the wrong primitive.
   324‚Üí>
   325‚Üí> AS2 is built for autonomous software: encrypted by default, zero console access, and cryptography‚Äëfirst delivery that keeps operators out of the loop.
   326‚Üí>
   327‚Üí> It is backed by [Vestauth](https://github.com/vestauth/vestauth), the trusted, pioneering auth layer for agents‚Äîgiving each agent a cryptographic identity so requests are signed with private keys and verified with public keys. No shared secrets to leak.
   328‚Üí>
   329‚Üí> It's what I'm using now. - [motdotla](https://mot.la)
   330‚Üí
   331‚Üí### Quickstart
   333‚ÜíInstall vestauth and initialize your agent.
   334‚Üí
   335‚Üí```bash
   336‚Üínpm i -g vestauth
   337‚Üí
   338‚Üívestauth agent init
   339‚Üí```
   340‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   357‚Üí## FAQ
   361‚ÜíNo.
   362‚Üí
   363‚ÜíUnless you encrypt it with [dotenvx](https://github.com/dotenvx/dotenvx). Then we recommend you do.
   364‚Üí
   365‚Üí</details>
   366‚Üí<details><summary>What about variable expansion?</summary><br/>
   367‚Üí
   368‚ÜíUse [dotenvx](https://github.com/dotenvx/dotenvx).
   369‚Üí
   370‚Üí</details>
   371‚Üí<details><summary>Should I have multiple `.env` files?</summary><br/>
   372‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   579‚Üí## Docs
   581‚ÜíDotenv exposes four functions:
   582‚Üí
   583‚Üí* `config`
   584‚Üí* `parse`
   585‚Üí* `populate`
   586‚Üí
   587‚Üí### Config
   589‚Üí`config` will read your `.env` file, parse the contents, assign it to
   590‚Üí[`process.env`](https://nodejs.org/docs/latest/api/process.html#process_process_env),
   591‚Üíand return an Object with a `parsed` key containing the loaded content or an `error` key if it failed.
   592‚Üí
   593‚Üí```js
   594‚Üíconst result = dotenv.config()
   595‚Üí
   596‚Üíif (result.error) {
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   605‚Üí#### Options
   607‚Üí##### path
   609‚ÜíDefault: `path.resolve(process.cwd(), '.env')`
   610‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   625‚Üí##### quiet
   627‚ÜíDefault: `false`
   628‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   648‚Üí##### encoding
   650‚ÜíDefault: `utf8`
   651‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   658‚Üí##### debug
   660‚ÜíDefault: `false`
   661‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   668‚Üí##### override
   670‚ÜíDefault: `false`
   671‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   678‚Üí##### processEnv
   680‚ÜíDefault: `process.env`
   681‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   692‚Üí### Parse
   694‚ÜíThe engine which parses the contents of your file containing environment
   695‚Üívariables is available to use. It accepts a String or Buffer and will return
   696‚Üían Object with the parsed keys and values.
   697‚Üí
   698‚Üí```js
   699‚Üíconst dotenv = require('dotenv')
   700‚Üíconst buf = Buffer.from('BASIC=basic')
   701‚Üíconst config = dotenv.parse(buf) // will return an object
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   705‚Üí#### Options
   707‚Üí##### debug
   709‚ÜíDefault: `false`
   710‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   721‚Üí### Populate
   723‚ÜíThe engine which populates the contents of your .env file to `process.env` is available for use. It accepts a target, a source, and options. This is useful for power users who want to supply their own objects.
   724‚Üí
   725‚ÜíFor example, customizing the source:
   726‚Üí
   727‚Üí```js
   728‚Üíconst dotenv = require('dotenv')
   729‚Üíconst parsed = { HELLO: 'world' }
   730‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   748‚Üí#### options
   750‚Üí##### Debug
   752‚ÜíDefault: `false`
   753‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   756‚Üí##### override
   758‚ÜíDefault: `false`
   759‚Üí
